  "doc_id": "33872",
  "text": "A slight reduction in the proportion of dihydroxylated forms was correlated with high day temperature in the first season of the experiment [CITATION_1] . In addition, another study from the same research group found small changes in profile due to reduction in amplitude between day and night temperatures [CITATION_2] . During stage I, an increase in the monohydroxylated forms was observed concomitant with a decrease in dihydroxylated forms. During stage II to III, an increase in dihydroxylation was observed concomitant with a decrease in trihydroxylated forms. Even though effects on the relative concentrations of flavonols vary, such findings suggest an adjustment in gene expression of the hydroxylase enzymes (F3H, F3'H, and F3'5'H), and will be discussed in the next section.",
